metadata.name: Panta Rei #187
metadata.description:
Everything changes, nothing stays the same, there is no absolute truth, the only reality is perennial movement.

Press 's' in live mode for high resolution png export.

Made with p5js, September, 2022.

Tagovi:

metadata.name: Mountaineering Diary Entries #17
metadata.description:
A lost game. A lost mountaineer. Maybe you will summit. Maybe an avalanche catches you on the descent. Maybe one day someone finds the camera in your pocket.

All images were made with DALLE-2 and Stable Diffusion and went through a Sinclair ZX Spectrum emulator. Diary entries were made with GPT-3.

Image Composition made with PureSpider template.

metadata.name: Hoppler #1
metadata.description:
Technological progress is always marked by how fast a vehicle moves, 
because humans love speed and that is why racing is one of the most famous sports in the world. 
But when the speed becomes too fast racing on earth means nothing anymore, 
where do we go next? 

Variations:
Two style of coloring
5 different zoom levels
Moon(4 kind)
Meteor(rare)
No stars background(rare)

Created using p5js

metadata.name: Invasion #218
metadata.description:
In September, like many of us, we remembered our school years, told each other about teachers, classmates, classes... And suddenly we realized that both did not like biology at school. And in vain. This is a very interesting and incredibly beautiful science. Inspired by school memories and beautiful infusoria slipper, we created this work.

By the way, some lucky ones can even have faces. Try your luck!

And one more thing. We would really like there to be more children in this world who will be able to discuss their favorite and unloved lessons. Therefore, 1/3 of the payment from sales will be transferred to the fund "Save the children"

metadata.name: Unstable Anticipation #70
metadata.description:
Minimal poster prints of blocks in motion.

Varying block arrangements fall from the canvas's top and interact with pegs near the bottom. After the animation completes, the scene is redrawn with a halftone pattern.

Matter JS is used to calculate the physics.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px

Features
* The length of the simulation
* Number, size, and position of the pegs
* Halftone grid size
* Varying amount of roughness for distorted halftone shapes
* Shape arrangement and composition
* 60/40% Color or monochrome

metadata.name: symphony redux #127
metadata.description:
subject to interpretation, but inspired by JAM Whistler's Nocturne in Black and Gold

symphony was released on fx(hash) on December 21, 2021, with largely broken preview images. symphony redux is an update of the symphony code, with working previews and a few extra features.

controls:
s -- save as png
space bar -- pause/unpause
1-6 -- pixel density

metadata.name: tr4ns4ctions #51
metadata.description:
Tr4ns4ctions is a series of real-time animations that use pixels to create an abstraction of the movement of values. The pixels are constantly rearranging, being transferred from offer to taker, liquify, appear and disappear. They are forming endless compositions, sometimes intransparent or with strange spins.

The level of abstraction has been set to a 2x pixel size and the color palette of the NES with 12 different color modes. 16 pixel patterns serve as the fundamental building blocks and a simplex noise field determines the direction of movement.

click || space => pause/unpause

View all tr4ns4ctions at https://tr4ns4ctions.com

Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: BlockonBlock #180
metadata.description:
‘BlockonBlock’ is the precursor and reserve pass for the upcoming ‘Hashway ‘69 Revisited’ collection by pixelwank. 
Free mint for pixelwank holders on tezos - After 3 days any remainders will be opened up to the public for 2tez.  

‘BlockonBlock’ was a study of rectangles following on from the use of circles in Generacci. 
Placements & building sizes are based on numbers from the fibonacci sequence. 

I had a blast making these and I hope they bring the collector as much enjoyment.

'Hashway '69 Revisited' coming soon :)

23 colour palettes 
14 colour overlays 
21% chance of extra lines
Click the image or press ‘s’ or ‘S’ in live move to save a 3000x3000 png 

Thanks for collectin’ & shoutouts to Circolors for the support <3 

R.I.F.F. 
Remember it’s for fun
